00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Welcome to this video tutorial on how to create subtitles.

2
00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:09.500
In this lesson, we'll learn the basics of SRT files.

3
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.000
An SRT file consists of subtitle text with timestamps.

4
00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:18.500
Each subtitle entry has a sequence number and time range.

5
00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:23.000
This helps synchronize subtitles with the video.

6
00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:27.500
Now you know the basics of creating an SRT file!
